<TEXT>
american scientists are finding rocks from the 
moon and perhaps mars in the glaciers of antarctica and one 
expert says they may have been slung into orbit by an asteroid 
collision during ancient times 
we are certain that these samples are from the moon said 
william cassidy a university of pittsburgh geologist 
the rocks deposited on ancient polar show fields hundreds of 
thousands of years ago match chemical characteristics of lunar 
samples collected by astronauts on the six apollo lunar missions he 
said matching the samples create what geologists call ground 
truth 
we dont know from where on the moon they came but we know 
they have to be from places more widespread than the four percent 
that weve sampled by apollo cassidy said tuesday at the 
international geological congress 
cassidy said it is believed that the antarctic moon rocks got to 
earth when in some ancient time an asteroid smashed into the lunar 
surface with such great violence that chunks of the moon were slung 
into orbit it would take less force to do this from the lunar 
surface because the moon has only onesixth of the earths gravity 
once in orbit the moon rocks could eventually be swept up by the 
earth the lunar material would streak through the atmosphere and 
then crash into the earths surface 
most such objects hit the oceans where they are lost or on land 
surfaces where they are weathered and eroded beyond recognition 
but in the antarctic time is frozen in gigantic sheets of ice 
that lie virtually unchanged for up to 20 million years moon rocks 
that come to rest there remain untouched and nearly pristine 
awaiting collection by cassidy and his team 
other types of rocks from space also are found on the frozen 
polar plains 
cassidy said two rare samples called shurgitites have been 
found that may have originated from mars 
we dont really know if thats the case because we dont have 
ground truth matched samples from a known source he said but 
cassidy said the fact that moon rocks hit earth support the idea 
that other samples could be from mars 
the lunar samples lend credence to the view that you really 
can hit a planet with an asteroid and knock off a meteoroid and get 
it into orbit he said this lends credence to the idea that the 
shurgitites could have come from mars and are really martian 
samples 
final proof he said will have to come from a sampling mission 
to mars 
cassidy said that about 12000 other types of meteorites have 
been gathered from the ice in antarctica he said he and his team 
find the space rocks by systematically searching using snowmobiles 
the meteorites are just lying around on the ice he said 
most are about the size of a large olive but some are as large 
as grapefruit 
the fragments are photographed collected in sealed bags and 
transported still frozen to the johnson space center in houston 
in a special laboratory there they are warmed and dried in a pure 
nitrogen atmosphere sections are cut from the samples and sent for 
study by scientists in 17 nations 
cassidy said when the study of antarctic meteorites first began 
20 years ago scientists hoped to find samples that were as old as 
the polar ice sheets where they were found 
we hoped we could look back 20 million years he said but 
the oldest one weve found is only about 900000 years old weve 
found two that are 700000 years old the bulk have fallen over just 
the last 300000 years 
and in a solar system more than four billion years old he said 
thats but a brief moment 
</TEXT>
