tests administered about 11 hours after the accident he is to be 
tried in october on felony and misdemeanor charges that include 
operating a vessel while intoxicated 
exxons report said the collison could have been avoided if the 
ship had been turned near a navigational light about three miles 
from bligh reef 
the company said it has not resolved a discrepancy involving 
information from a course recorder and testimony given the ntsb by 
