to the private banks after brady announce his plans in march 
the banks reportedly have offered a 35 percent reduction but 
only on the condition the multinational world bank and the 
international monetary fund guarantee the interest payments on the 
remaining balance 
however the agreement between bush and the leaders of the six 
other industrial powers provides only limited interest support 
by their taxpayers through the imf and world bank for transactions 
involving significant debt and debt service reduction 
