communist leader gen wojciech jaruzelski 
was elected wednesday to the countrys powerful new presidency by a 
slim margin in the national assembly 
jaruzelski the only candidate was helped by a boycott by some 
opposition lawmakers the vote was 270 for 233 against and 34 
abstaining there were 537 valid votes and 269 were required to 
win the communist coalition has a 300259 majority in the assembly 
government ministers gave one another a thumbsup sign as word 
spread through the chamber while the paper ballots were counted and 
recounted 
i state that citizen wojciech jaruzelski has received the 
required number of votes and has been elected by the national 
assembly to be the president of the polish peoples republic 
parliament speaker mikolaj kozakiewicz said after the vote 
the post gives jaruzelski the communist party leader control of 
the military and foreign relations and allows him to nominate the 
next prime minister the office has a sixyear term 
