wednesday to restore to public housing authorities the power to 
evict drug criminals from federally funded public housing 
the measure sponsored by sens daniel p moynihan dny and 
alfonse damato rny was added to the foreign relations 
authorization act of 1990 
today we have restored the original intent of my provision to 
last years drug bill moynihan said afterward dont let it be 
said that we didnt get tough we drew the line now we can work 
toward our original goal of demanding accountability 
during final consideration of the 1989 supplemental 
appropriations bill in june language was added to limit moynihans 
original eviction provision in the antidrug abuse act of 1988 both 
moynihan and damato voted for the supplemental not realizing they 
were voting to undo the eviction measure damato said at a news 
conference monday in new york 
the new provision restores the ability of federal officials to 
waive administrative hearings for drug criminals when the hearings 
would duplicate eviction proceedings in state courts 
by passing this amendment we are saying that we will no longer 
subsidize violence and criminal activity in public housing 
moynihan said wednesday 
in considering the same foreign relations authorization bill the 
senate unanimously passed a moynihan amendment offering political 
and financial assistance to burmese students 
