a judge on wednesday granted a research 
labs request to silence a former technician who complained about 
safety and health procedures more than a year before another worker 
died of a rare virus 
international research and development corp won a preliminary 
injunction in van buren county circuit court against james casey in 
connection with a lawsuit the company filed against casey and david 
bailey last september 
irdc alleges the men violated a confidentiality agreement with 
the company by giving statements some of which the company says 
are false to government investigators who were inspecting the 
company 
judge meyer warshawsky ruled that irdc could suffer irreparable 
harm to its reputation if casey continued making allegations against 
the mattawan company 
warshawsky warned bailey not to discuss the case but did not 
include him in the injunction irdc had sought to silence bailey as 
well 
