administration about health and safety problems at the lab 
resulting in several citations and a loss of business irdc 
attorneys said 
warshawsky said that on monday he would set a date for the trial 
of irdcs lawsuit 
casey has countersued the company contending he was exposed to 
dangers at the lab and was fired in retaliation for his complaints 
about safety problems 
the court action comes one month after the death of a technician 
who contracted a rare virus from an infected research monkey 
another former irdc technician is hospitalized with the infection 
the deadly herpes b virus 
the company alleges statements made by casey and bailey have 
contributed to bad publicity and death threats from animal rights 
groups 
attorneys for bailey and casey said their clients right to free 
speech outweighs any harm that might come to the company 
the independent contract research laboratory tests drugs and 
chemicals for medical pharmaceutical veterinary and agriculture 
companies 
