noted that bush supports the decision on the computers 
the commerce department announced tuesday that it was removing 
export controls on atcompatible and similar desktop personal 
computers to noncommunist nations 
it said the administration will also propose to the 17nation 
coordinating committee on multilateral export controls cocom that 
export restrictions be lifted against the soviet bloc nations 
cheney said he would prefer that exports be permitted for a 
lower level of technology 
mosbacher in a statement released tuesday said bushs trip to 
poland and hungary had paved the way for expanding trade in areas 
that improve prospects for prosperity in eastern europe without 
harming americas national security 
eliminating export controls on atcompatible personal computers 
is one way to meet this objective he said consistent with the 
spirit of the presidents initiatives we are creating new 
opportunities for us manufacturers to sell more widely abroad 
the at is an ibm model that was widely emulated 
the department said regulations removing the controls on exports 
to western nations will appear in the federal register on july 18 
and be effective immediately 
the cocom committee based in paris consists of australia 
belgium britain canada denmark france west germany greece 
italy japan luxembourg netherlands norway portugal spain 
turkey and the united states 
the net result of this decontrol is to focus and maintain 
export restrictions on those items that are truly strategic and 
that we can control effectively mosbacher said 
in this case these computers are available in 11 countries and 
from 70 vendors outside cocom countries he added those countries 
include hungary and czechoslovakia in the east bloc 
the department said there were about 6 million atcompatible desk 
top personal computers sold worldwide by us companies in 1988 of 
those 27 million worth more than 1 billion were sold outside the 
united states 
