houstonbased texas air also announced a complicated mix of 
transactions in which continental soon would purchase 11 widebody 
airbus a300 jets and spare parts from eastern for 3035 million 
continental also would lease two mcdonnell douglas dc10s from 
eastern and lease 34 jets back to its sister carrier 
i think this is an important step in continentals return to 
profitability and confidence in the future of the airline d 
joseph corr continentals chairman and chief executive officer 
told a news conference 
what were really doing is not only restructuring our fleet 
but were also at the same time providing for our fleet way out into 
the future corr said overall were looking at more seats to 
more destinations than prior to these changes 
under the deal houstonbased continental agreed to buy as many 
as 60 of boeing cos narrowbody 737300s with deliveries of 30 
aircraft planned for 1992 to 1994 and with an option to purchase 
another 30 of the jets in 1995 and 1996 
total cost of the continental purchase would be about 17 
billion corr said adding that about threequarters of the new 
fleet would replace aging aircraft 
corr declined to discuss financing for the purchase continental 
posted a firstquarter loss of 165 million narrowed from an 806 
million loss in the same quarter of 1988 
continental a nonunion carrier which emerged from bankruptcy 
reorganization in september 1986 and miamibased eastern were among 
only three major us airlines that did not have new planes on order 
prior to the boeing deal announced wednesday pan am corp is the 
third carrier 
corr said the federal bankruptcy judge overseeing easterns 
reorganization burton r lifland probably will have the final say 
over the airlines finances but he said continentals negotiations 
on an order for eastern planes had nothing to do with its sister 
carriers financial status 
the agreement with boeing allows continental to substitute a 
portion of its order for boeings 737400s or 737500s which have 
different seat capacities allowing for greater flexibility as the 
airlines needs change in the coming years corr said 
he insisted that the prices were fair market value denying any 
suggestion that the arrangement was part of a shift in assets at the 
expense of crippled eastern 
